            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice <strong>half </strong>your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> into rounds</p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining tomato</strong> in half</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1716201316834-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1716201316834-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1716201316834-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1716201316834-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-1716201316834-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the potatoes from the microwave and add your <strong>southern fried seasoning</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Transfer the <strong>seasoned potatoes</strong> to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Add the<strong> tomato halves </strong>(seed-side up!) with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong>, a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and a small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15 min or until the potatoes are crisp – these are your <strong>hash potatoes & roasted tomatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-1716201320158-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
